language: East Sumbanese, Umbu Ratu Nggai dialect

annotation: to dig out (a tree, etc. but not ditch)

language: Kadazan Dusun of Taginambur, Kota Belud, Sabah, Malaysia

annotation: most probably borrowed from Malay on account of g instead of *k
The prenasalization is a morphematic feature
PHF - to dig in the earth
to dig up, dig out, harvest (yams)
To dig, excavate, hollow, shell (e.g. pick nose, pluck out eye) (Fts)
dig a hole with a digging implement
The distinction between those two lexical items is not clear in the source lexicon
L, VLP: ye'i WB: koda, èka
